## Third-Party Services and Libraries

This project integrates with the following third-party services and libraries:

### Spotify Web API
- **Service**: Spotify Web API for music streaming and user library access
- **Terms**: https://developer.spotify.com/terms/
- **Documentation**: https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api/
- **Usage**: Search music, access user playlists, control playback
- **Authentication**: OAuth2 with user consent

### YouTube Data API v3
- **Service**: YouTube Data API for music video search and metadata
- **Terms**: https://developers.google.com/youtube/terms/api-services-terms-of-service
- **Documentation**: https://developers.google.com/youtube/v3
- **Usage**: Search music videos, retrieve video metadata
- **Rate Limits**: Subject to YouTube API quotas

### Font Awesome Icons
- **Library**: Font Awesome Free icons
- **License**: Font Awesome Free License
- **Website**: https://fontawesome.com/license/free
- **Usage**: UI icons throughout the application

### Unsplash Images
- **Service**: Unsplash for sample artwork and images
- **License**: Unsplash License
- **Website**: https://unsplash.com/license
- **Usage**: Sample album artwork and background images

### Web APIs and Standards
- **HTML5 Audio API**: Native browser audio playback
- **Web Audio API**: Audio analysis and visualization
- **Fetch API**: HTTP requests for API integration
- **Local Storage API**: Client-side data persistence
- **Canvas API**: Audio visualization rendering

## Audio Content and Copyright Notice

### Important Legal Information

This software is designed as a platform for music playback and discovery. Users are responsible for ensuring they have proper rights and licenses for any audio content used with this software.

### Supported Content Types
- **Personal Music Library**: User-owned audio files
- **API-Sourced Content**: Music accessed through official APIs (Spotify, YouTube)
- **Sample Content**: Demo tracks for development and testing purposes only

### User Responsibilities
- Ensure compliance with local copyright laws
- Respect terms of service for integrated APIs
- Obtain proper licenses for commercial use
- Use personal music files within fair use guidelines

### Platform Disclaimers
- This software does not host, store, or distribute copyrighted music
- All API integrations require user authentication and consent
- Users must comply with each service provider's terms of use
- The platform facilitates access to legally available content only

## API Usage and Compliance

### Rate Limiting and Fair Use
- All API calls are subject to provider rate limits
- Implement caching to minimize unnecessary requests
- Respect API quotas and usage guidelines
- Monitor and handle API errors gracefully

### Data Privacy and Security
- No personal data is collected or transmitted by this software
- API credentials are stored locally only
- User preferences and playlists remain on user's device
- No tracking, analytics, or data mining features

### Authentication and Authorization
- OAuth2 flows require explicit user consent
- Tokens are managed securely within the browser
- No server-side storage of user credentials
- Users can revoke access at any time

## Development and Contribution Guidelines

### Code Quality Standards
- Follow modern JavaScript ES6+ practices
- Implement responsive CSS with mobile-first approach
- Use semantic HTML and proper accessibility features
- Maintain clean, documented, and modular code

### Security Best Practices
- Never commit API keys or secrets to version control
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Implement proper error handling for all API calls
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs

### Testing and Quality Assurance
- Test across multiple browsers and devices
- Verify accessibility compliance
- Performance test audio loading and playback
- Validate API integration error handling

## Support and Maintenance

### Community Guidelines
- Issues and feature requests welcome via GitHub
- Contributions subject to code review
- Maintain respectful and constructive communication
- Help others learn and improve their skills

### Maintenance Commitment
- Regular updates for security and compatibility
- Bug fixes for critical issues
- Documentation improvements
- API integration updates as needed

